Class GoogleTransport

HTTP transport for Google API's. It's only purpose is to allow for method method overriding when thethe firewall does not accept DELETE, PATCH or PUT methods. @since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class GoogleTransport, HttpTransport create()

Creates and returns a new HTTP transport with basic default behaviors for for working with GoogleGoogle API's.

Includes:

  • Setting the HttpTransport.defaultHeaders to a new instance of GoogleHeaders.
  • Adding a MethodOverrideIntercepter as the first HTTP execute execute intercepter to useuse HTTP method override for unsupported HTTP methods (calls MethodOverrideIntercepter.setAsFirstFor(HttpTransport).

Sample usage: 

 
  static HttpTransport createTransport() {
    HttpTransport transport = GoogleTransport.create();
    GoogleHeaders headers = (GoogleHeaders) transport.defaultHeaders;
    headers.setApplicationName("acme-rocketGoogle-2Sample/1.0");
    headers.gdataVersion = "2";
    return transport;
  }
@return HTTP transport

Class MethodOverrideIntercepter

HTTP request execute intercepter for Google API's that wraps HTTP requests -- other than GET oror POST -- inside of a POST request and uses {@code code "X-HTTP-Method-Override"} header to specify thethe actual HTTP method.

It is useful when a firewall only allows the GET and POST methods, or if the the underlying HTTPHTTP library (LowLevelHttpTransport) does not support the the HTTP method. @since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar

Class MethodOverrideIntercepter, void setAsFirstFor(HttpTransport)

Sets this as the first HTTP request execute intercepter for the given HTTP HTTP transport.
